      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, my apologies for the goblin misdirection. The \"gibberish gremlins\" were merely a whimsical way to describe the mysterious ailments affecting your tomato plants. No need to worry about actual goblins; let's focus on the gremlins of the garden world.\n\nAs for checking the pH, you don't need a full-blown goblin spellbook, just a simple soil test kit. These kits are like the enchanted mirrors of the gardening world, revealing the hidden truths of your soil's pH level. You can find these kits at your local garden center or online. Once you've got your kit, follow the instructions carefully, as if you're deciphering an ancient goblin riddle. The results will tell you if your soil's pH is too acidic or too alkaline, and from there, you can adjust it with the appropriate amendments, like lime or sulfur, to bring your soil back into balance.\n\nRemember, even the most powerful goblin wizards need the right tools to cast their spells. So, arm yourself with your soil test kit, and you'll be well on your way to taming the gremlins in your garden. Good luck, and may your tomato plants flourish once more!",
